President Barack Obama has granted commutations of sentence to 22 individuals. These individuals had been convicted of various drug-related offenses and were serving lengthy prison sentences. The commutations mean that their sentences will expire on July 28, 2015. Some of the offenses included conspiracy to distribute cocaine base, conspiracy to distribute crack cocaine, possession with intent to distribute cocaine base, conspiracy to possess with intent to distribute methamphetamine, and conspiracy to possess with intent to distribute cocaine and heroin. The individuals were from various states including Illinois, Florida, Texas, Kansas, California, Georgia, Virginia, Kentucky, Tennessee, Alabama, Michigan, Washington D.C., North Carolina, Ohio, and Iowa.